30:18.517 --> 30:21.684
Okay. Maybe if you didn't rush me.

30:23.689 --> 30:27.093
Don't rush you. Okay. I can use that.

30:27.393 --> 30:29.962
See, Rick, they've done studies

30:30.062 --> 30:34.033
and they found that in any system that
relies on cooperation from a school of fish,

30:34.133 --> 30:36.469
say, or even a professional
hockey team, for example,

30:36.569 --> 30:39.338
these experts have
identified communication

30:39.438 --> 30:42.105
as the number one single key to success.

30:49.548 --> 30:51.782
You know what "fear" stands for?

30:52.351 --> 30:53.285
What?

30:53.385 --> 30:56.086
"False Evidence Appearing Real."

30:58.791 --> 31:00.726
You're going really fucking fast, dude.

31:00.826 --> 31:03.529
Get out of your head, Rick.
It's a bad neighborhood.

31:03.629 --> 31:06.098
Now, when you get a chance,
I'd like to know where we're going.

31:06.198 --> 31:08.708
Left on Third. Six blocks.

31:14.940 --> 31:18.477
Find a more appropriate place to park
the car, and don't get blocked in.

31:18.577 --> 31:20.379
Are you the one that made the call?

31:20.479 --> 31:21.714
No, no. I think...

31:21.814 --> 31:24.683
I was trying to go to sleep,
and I heard a sound.

31:24.783 --> 31:26.685
It scared me. That's why I called.

31:26.785 --> 31:30.053
- Sir, what's going on?
- Who the fuck are you?

31:35.527 --> 31:38.998
- TV news. What happened?
- It was a shooting.

31:39.198 --> 31:43.233
I told the cops that he was waving a gun
last week, but they didn't fucking care.

31:44.036 --> 31:46.238
Can you try one more
time without swearing?

31:46.338 --> 31:49.575
- I'm not doing it again.
- But this is for TV.

31:49.775 --> 31:51.577
Yeah? I don't have a TV.

32:01.853 --> 32:03.422
It's over.

32:03.522 --> 32:05.455
Shot the place to shit.

32:13.733 --> 32:16.435
All right, guys, pack it up.
Let's move it out.

32:16.535 --> 32:20.403
...running out of there as fast as
we could. Through that window there.

33:26.571 --> 33:28.189
<i>Great shot.</i>

33:30.742 --> 33:32.675
Oh, that's fantastic.

33:33.078 --> 33:35.634
Oh, that's a great piece of tape.

33:36.381 --> 33:39.685
- You didn't get an interview with the couple?
- I have footage of them.

33:39.785 --> 33:42.754
I have an interview with a neighbor.
She curses, but you can cut that out.

33:42.854 --> 33:44.756
How did you get inside the house?

33:44.856 --> 33:46.725
- The door was open.
- They allowed you?

33:46.825 --> 33:49.328
I heard somebody yell to come in,
and when nobody was inside, I left.

33:49.428 --> 33:51.297
And the only shot of the couple
is through a window?

33:51.497 --> 33:53.825
- The police were shutting it down.
- I don't like it.

33:53.925 --> 33:56.201
- Like what?
- The footage looks like he broke in.

33:56.301 --> 33:58.738
There's no close-up of the homeowners
and he's giving us their name

33:58.838 --> 34:01.740
- off a piece of private correspondence.
- Excuse me, that's junk mail.

34:01.840 --> 34:04.777
- Well, I have a problem with that.
- We'll knock out a killer package.

34:04.877 --> 34:06.445
- This is my job.
- No!

34:06.545 --> 34:09.715
Your job is writing the tweet of the day.
And getting Deb to turn sideways

34:09.815 --> 34:13.018
during the weather forecast.
We're running it.

34:13.418 --> 34:17.556
I like how you handled Frank.
You didn't soften the truth or dilute it.

34:17.656 --> 34:19.491
I think being clear with your
objectives is more important

34:19.591 --> 34:23.295
than trying to present your ideas
in a non-confrontational manner.

34:23.395 --> 34:27.632
- Do you have experience in an office?
- Myself? Not presently, no.

34:27.733 --> 34:30.635
- Where did you get all that?
- I study a lot online.

34:30.735 --> 34:33.272
- Yeah? Like what?
- All sorts of things, actually.

34:33.371 --> 34:35.290
I'm on my computer all day.

34:36.475 --> 34:38.444
I haven't had what you'd call
much of a formal education,

34:38.543 --> 34:41.139
but you can find most anything
if you look hard enough.

34:48.654 --> 34:52.690
Last year, I took an online
business course, for example.

34:52.791 --> 34:57.629
And I learned that you have to have a
business plan before starting a business.

34:57.729 --> 35:02.865
And that why you pursue something is
equally as important as what you pursue.

35:03.835 --> 35:06.238
The site advised you to...

35:06.638 --> 35:10.142
answer the following question before you
decide where to focus your abilities.

35:10.242 --> 35:14.243
The question was "What do I love to do?"

35:15.180 --> 35:18.083
The site suggested making a list
of your strengths and weaknesses.

35:18.183 --> 35:21.487
What am I good at?
What am I not good at?

35:21.587 --> 35:23.489
Maybe I want to strengthen
and develop knowledge

35:23.589 --> 35:27.390
about the things I'm already good at.
Maybe I want to strengthen my weaknesses.

35:33.265 --> 35:35.408
I recently remade my list.

35:36.735 --> 35:39.004
And I'm thinking

35:39.304 --> 35:41.607
that television news

35:41.907 --> 35:44.810
might just be something I love

35:44.910 --> 35:47.677
as well as something
I happen to be good at.

36:00.725 --> 36:03.359
On TV, it looks so real.

36:04.229 --> 36:06.376
Yes. It does.

36:07.766 --> 36:12.504
Well, I have a show to do.
Your check is at the desk.

36:12.604 --> 36:14.940
Outstanding work, Lou.
Really, just great.

36:15.040 --> 36:17.941
Thanks, Nina. That means an awful lot.

36:19.478 --> 36:20.710
Okay.

