01:47:23.504 --> 01:47:27.508
I got a cop near death in the hospital,
three dead, four wounded,

01:47:27.608 --> 01:47:31.045
and a dozen major crimes stretching
a mile of Third. This tape is evidence.

01:47:31.245 --> 01:47:34.315
It's news footage bought and paid for
from an independent contractor.

01:47:34.415 --> 01:47:35.583
And how do you think he got it?

01:47:35.683 --> 01:47:38.319
- If there's an issue, speak to him.
- Don't get in the way of this.

01:47:38.419 --> 01:47:41.055
Unless you have a judge's order,
we're going with it in four minutes.

01:47:41.355 --> 01:47:44.159
Hey. Isn't that him?

01:47:48.996 --> 01:47:51.002
Camera One, stay centered up.

01:47:53.000 --> 01:47:54.933
Camera Two, we'll do a
zoom out when we come out.

01:47:56.237 --> 01:47:57.822
Joel has got a source on the taskforce

01:47:57.922 --> 01:48:00.542
who says they found drugs
at the Granada Hills house.

01:48:00.642 --> 01:48:04.245
Cocaine in wrapped packages hidden
in crawlspaces. Over 50 pounds.

01:48:04.345 --> 01:48:07.148
And he confirmed it with an
investigator at the scene.

01:48:07.248 --> 01:48:09.951
It wasn't a home invasion.
It was a drug robbery.

01:48:10.051 --> 01:48:11.861
Give it to the noon crew.

01:48:12.887 --> 01:48:15.190
- This is news.
- It detracts from the story.

01:48:15.290 --> 01:48:17.158
It is the story.

01:48:17.258 --> 01:48:21.530
The story is urban crime creeping
into the suburbs. That's the story.

01:48:22.630 --> 01:48:25.366
- Jesus, you sound like Lou.
- Ten seconds to back.

01:48:25.466 --> 01:48:29.137
I think Lou is inspiring all
of us to reach a little higher.

01:48:29.237 --> 01:48:32.087
Five, four, three,

01:48:32.187 --> 01:48:34.548
two, one. Sting it.

01:48:36.310 --> 01:48:38.477
Mics. Dissolve.

01:48:49.490 --> 01:48:53.427
You understand that you've been read
your rights, and you're here voluntarily?

01:48:53.527 --> 01:48:55.471
That's right. Yes.

01:48:56.163 --> 01:48:58.300
And this is being recorded and filmed?

01:48:59.000 --> 01:49:01.166
<i>Yes, from the camera up there.</i>

01:49:01.569 --> 01:49:03.770
<i>Wide angle.</i>

01:49:08.375 --> 01:49:11.312
Would you tell me how it is you were
at the Chinatown Express tonight

01:49:11.412 --> 01:49:12.880
and called the 911?

01:49:12.980 --> 01:49:16.114
Of course. It began earlier in the day.

01:49:17.184 --> 01:49:19.189
I was watering my plant.

01:49:20.387 --> 01:49:22.757
I looked out my window at my apartment.

01:49:22.857 --> 01:49:25.827
The one you visited. And...

01:49:25.927 --> 01:49:29.130
I saw a dark-colored vehicle with two
men inside parked across the street.

01:49:29.230 --> 01:49:31.537
I didn't think anything of it,
otherwise I would have reported it then.

01:49:33.234 --> 01:49:36.292
We began our night, my...

01:49:38.372 --> 01:49:40.908
employee and myself.

01:49:41.008 --> 01:49:44.011
And around approximately 12:38,

01:49:44.111 --> 01:49:48.215
I looked in my rearview mirror and I
saw what looked like the same men

01:49:48.315 --> 01:49:51.686
in the same vehicle following us.
I made an evasive maneuver.

01:49:51.786 --> 01:49:54.689
I circled back and tailed
them to the restaurant.

01:49:54.789 --> 01:49:56.869
At which point, I saw them
go inside and recognized them

01:49:56.969 --> 01:49:59.474
as the same men from the home invasion.

01:50:00.327 --> 01:50:03.798
You told me you didn't see the men.
That you didn't get a good look at them.

01:50:04.098 --> 01:50:07.168
Well, it all came back to me
when I saw them going in.

01:50:07.268 --> 01:50:10.438
Their shapes and their movements.

01:50:10.538 --> 01:50:12.974
And then I saw that one of the men
had a gun under his shirt,

01:50:13.074 --> 01:50:16.243
so I immediately got my
phone and dialed 911.

01:50:16.343 --> 01:50:17.478
That's your story?

01:50:17.578 --> 01:50:19.947
That's what happened.
That's why I'm sitting here with you.

01:50:20.047 --> 01:50:23.384
I think that the men
saw my footage and...

01:50:23.484 --> 01:50:25.687
they tracked me down.

01:50:25.987 --> 01:50:28.120
You want to know what I think?

01:50:29.123 --> 01:50:31.125
Yes, please.

01:50:31.325 --> 01:50:34.079
I think you withheld information.

01:50:34.562 --> 01:50:37.598
I think you saw the two men in
the murder house in Granada Hills

01:50:37.698 --> 01:50:41.536
and you saw the car and you sat on it

01:50:41.836 --> 01:50:44.005
to get something you could film.

01:50:44.405 --> 01:50:46.471
What do you think about that?

01:50:48.008 --> 01:50:50.011
I think that would be...

01:50:50.111 --> 01:50:52.813
a very unprofessional thing
for me to do in my business.

01:50:52.913 --> 01:50:54.982
It would be murder.

01:50:55.282 --> 01:50:58.019
I can understand why you're looking into it,
but I didn't do anything like that.

01:50:58.119 --> 01:51:01.899
- Nothing that could be considered wrong.
- You don't fool me for a minute.

01:51:01.999 --> 01:51:06.327
- I'm glad.
- I think everything you said is a lie.

01:51:06.727 --> 01:51:08.779
I wish my partner was here
to back up what happened.

01:51:08.879 --> 01:51:10.498
You left your dead partner.

01:51:10.598 --> 01:51:13.334
No, the ambulances arrived.
They're trained professionals.

01:51:13.434 --> 01:51:15.832
Yeah, and you seem real
broken up about that.

01:51:16.170 --> 01:51:17.505
No...

01:51:17.705 --> 01:51:20.038
He died doing what he loved.

01:51:21.075 --> 01:51:23.912
You filmed him dying.

01:51:25.513 --> 01:51:27.682
<i>Yeah. That's what I do. It's my job.</i>

01:51:27.782 --> 01:51:31.383
<i>I like to say that if you're seeing me,
you're having the worst day of your life.</i>

01:52:04.151 --> 01:52:07.455
<i>Any Rampart unit, ambulance to
11 Rampart on Second Avenue.</i>

01:52:07.555 --> 01:52:10.255
<i>Victim, female, white.
Unknown property taken.</i>

01:52:29.109 --> 01:52:30.742
<i>Congratulations.</i>

01:52:32.947 --> 01:52:35.051
Congratulations.

